How was the ordering experience? I went past the seating to the back of the restaurant where the cashier was stationed. I ordered and another employee had to come out to better understand my American accent (they all spoke English, but the WAY I spoke English threw some of them off). I grabbed a seat and waited. I would suggest calling in your order ahead of time (if you aren’t afraid of those Yelp reviews). Overall, the ordering experience was pleasant. My food was ready in about 15 minutes. The podcast I was listening to wasn’t even over yet!  How delicious was the food? Delicious! The bread was the first thing that stuck out to me. It was that flaky, crispy hero bread that is so amazing. Biting in, the steak flavors, the sauces, the veggies on there. Wow. So good. My fiance was in total agreement as well. This thing was awesome  Did it fill me up for $5 or less? It absolutely filled me up. The final cost was $5 with no tax – right on the cusp of the Cheap Eats cutoff. But it was so good that it was worth going to the brink of what I was willing to pay. And in the grand scheme of New York food, this is a steal.  Conclusion: If you are a steak sandwich person, check this out. I do want to try their chicken sandwich, ham and cheese sandwich, and Cuban sandwich as well. It was so good that I have faith that their other offerings will be delicious as well.
